To import existing source code that doesn't have an eclipse project file follow the
following easy steps:
- Step 1:- Open Eclipse. 
Step 2:- Create a new Empty Java Project into the Workspace. 
Step 3:- Select General and then Project. 
Step 4:-Write the project Name. 
Step 5:- Now right click on the source folder and choose import and then general and file system. 
Step 6:- Choose your files or browse your file from the system. 
Step 7:- Now open .java file & edit (or run).
Follow these simple steps to import an existing Java project in eclipse. Enjoy
running your projects.
